BoM ID*
A structured list of all the components, and their quantities that make up a parent product or order.
Enter a unique, numeric or alphanumeric key to identify the bill of material.
Type: Text Length: 40(80) - see introduction

Variant ID*
A structured subset of the specific input products that are used to manufacture an output product.
Only variants can be used in a production model and later in manufacturing. In a production BoM, the same input product can be used in more than one variant.
Variants can be defined for different output products, but usually the output products are similar. For example, a production BoM can be defined for all engines fora particular model of car. The variants can be defined for individual engine types, for example, a variant can be defined for a1. 6 liter engine, and another variant for a 2. 0 liter engine. By using variants in this way, the maintenance of all the input products for similar output products is reduced.
Type: Text Length: 8(80) - see introduction

Product ID in BoM variant*
Unique alphanumeric key assigned to a product within a bill of material variant.
With this product ID you define the product that is manufactured with a BoM variant in a production process.
Type: Text Length: 80

Product Specification ID
A document with a detailed description of the properties that characterize a product.
Enter the unique, alphanumeric ID of the product specification document.
Type: Text Length: 80

Quantity
A definite amount or measure of an item, for example, a product.
Type: Number Length: 31 Decimal: 5

Line Item Group ID*
Type: Text Length: 40(80) - see introduction

Line Item BoM*
A position in a production bill of material in which an input product and its quantity can be specified.
Line items are independent of variants. The same line item ID can be used in more than one production bill of material variant.
Type: Text Length: 8(80) - see introduction

Input Product ID*
Unique alphanumeric key assigned to an input product in a bill of material.
With the input product ID you define the material of components that are used to produce the product of this BoM variant.
Type: Text Length: 80

Quantity*
A definite amount or measure of an item, for example, a product.
Type: Number Length: 31 Decimal: 5

Quantity UoM*
Enter the same unit of measure as for the Supply Planning UoM in the material master data (Materials migration object).
Type: Text Length: 80

Engineering Change Order ID*
A directive to change the product content of a production bill of material.
Before the input products controlled by an engineeringchange order (ECO) can be used in the system: The validity date on which the system automatically implements changes must be reached The ECO must be at the status of Completed
Within one bill of material, only one Engineering Change Order ID is allowed. The ECO must be at the status of Completed.
Type: Text Length: 12(80) - see introduction

Fixed Quantity Indicator
A setting that ensures the quantity specified for an input product in a production BoM variant stays constant, regardless of how large the requirement is for the output product.
This is an indicator field. To activate enter 'X'. If not, leave it empty.
Type: Text Length: 1

Deleted
This indicator field enables you to set the line item inactive. To do so, enter 'X'. Otherwise, leave the field empty.
Type: Text Length: 1
